1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,145
When you start the activities, they will follow the same order as this lesson.

2
00:00:05,095 --> 00:00:13,750
First, you do a warm-up: Choose a real list: shopping, medication reminders, jobs, appointments or packing.

3
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:18,328
Then you answer quick checks, so we know the key words make sense.

4
00:00:18,328 --> 00:00:25,013
Next, you practise the real computer skill: Create a bulleted list with at least four items.

5
00:00:25,013 --> 00:00:27,633
Practise Enter for a new bullet.

6
00:00:27,633 --> 00:00:34,184
You may also type a short answer, for example: Type the file type that keeps a layout the same.

7
00:00:34,184 --> 00:00:40,339
At the end, you finish with a stretch or reflection: Use Save As and choose PDF.

8
00:00:40,339 --> 00:00:44,945
Staff may stop before final saving if using a shared device.

9
00:00:44,945 --> 00:00:47,496
Take one activity at a time.

10
00:00:47,496 --> 00:00:52,051
If you need help, ask staff, then try the next step yourself.

